    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-21T11:14:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-21T11:14:00-05:00" n="419"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/949</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-21T11:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 21, 1918, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s March 19, 6 p.m. Fully answered in my March 14, 4 p.m., except as to
                    the effect of publication upon public feeling which has been exceedingly
                    prejudicial. Newspaper comment bitter.</p>
                <p>I am astonished that the Minister for Foreign Affairs expressed regrets through
                    Ecuadoran Minister and not through this Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
